org.mundo.agent
Class Agent

java.lang.Object
  org.mundo.rt.Service
      org.mundo.agent.Agent
All Implemented Interfaces:
IMobility, IEmits
public class Agent
extends Service
implements IMobility

A mobile agent is a service that can move autonomously through the network. Concrete agent implementations derive from this class. The agent class supports the following functionalities:

  • Code Migration: A concrete implementation of an agent must be packaged into a plug-in component. When the agent is migrated to a new location, the associated plug-in will be sent over to the new node and be deployed there, dynamically at runtime.
  • State Migration: Agents transport their internal state between different nodes by means of object serialization.

erwin

Instantiates a new agent. Because agent classes come from plug-ins, they can only be constructed with such reflection-style calls.
